{
  "local_port": 49364,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Bank Accounts: How do I know whether my bank account is linked to my Aadhaar card or not?",
  "response": "To check whether your bank account is linked to your Aadhaar card, you can use one of the following methods:\n\n### 1. **Check via Internet Banking or Mobile Banking**\n   - Log in to your bank's **Internet Banking** or **Mobile Banking** app.\n   - Navigate to the section for **account details** or **profile settings**.\n   - Look for an option like **Aadhaar linking status** or **Aadhaar details**.\n   - If your Aadhaar number is displayed, it means your account is linked to your Aadhaar.\n\n### 2. **Visit Your Bank Branch**\n   - Visit your bank branch with your **Aadhaar card** and **bank account details**.\n   - Request the bank staff to check whether your Aadhaar is linked to your account.\n\n### 3. **Use UIDAI\u2019s Online Portal**\n   - Visit the **UIDAI (Unique Identification Authority of India)** official website: [https://uidai.gov.in/](https://uidai.gov.in/).\n   - Go to the **Aadhaar Services** section and click on **Check Aadhaar & Bank Account Linking Status**.\n   - Enter your **Aadhaar number** and the **security code** provided.\n   - An **OTP** will be sent to your registered mobile number. Enter the OTP to verify.\n   - The portal will display whether your Aadhaar is linked to your bank account.\n\n### 4. **Check via SMS**\n   - Open your messaging app and send an SMS to **567676** in the following format:\n     ```\n     UID STATUS <Your 12-digit Aadhaar Number>\n     ```\n   Example: `UID STATUS 123456789012`\n   - You will receive a reply SMS confirming whether your Aadhaar is linked to your bank account.\n\n### 5. **Call Your Bank\u2019s Customer Care**\n   - Contact your bank\u2019s customer care helpline.\n   - Provide your **bank account details** and **Aadhaar number** to the representative.\n   - They will verify and confirm the linking status for you.\n\n### Note:\nEnsure that your Aadhaar number is correctly linked to your mobile number, as it is required for OTP-based verification processes. If your Aadhaar is not linked, you can visit your bank branch or use online/mobile banking to link it.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
